TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hou, Kewei
AU  - Mo, Haitao
AU  - Xue, Chen
AU  - Zhang, Lu
T1  - Which Factors?*
PY  - 2019
Y1  - 2019/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfy032
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 23
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 35
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Many recently proposed, seemingly different factor models are closely related. In spanning tests, the q-factor model largely subsumes the Fama–French five- and six-factor models, and the q5 model subsumes the Stambaugh–Yuan four-factor model. Their “mispricing” factors are sensitive to the construction procedure, and once replicated via the traditional approach, are close to the q-factors, with correlations of 0.8 and 0.84. Finally, consistent with the investment CAPM, valuation theory predicts a positive relation between the expected investment and the expected return.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfy032
ER  - 



